cyclone.name: NESTOR
cyclone.current_location: about 430 miles southwest of the mouth of the Mississippi River
cyclone.trajectory: tracking northeast toward the northern Gulf Coast, then expected to sweep across north-central Florida and the southeastern United States before reaching the Atlantic off the Carolinas

weather_observation.watch_coast: Tropical Storm Warning: Mississippi/Alabama border to Yankeetown, FL and Grand Isle, LA to the Mouth of the Pearl River
weather_observation.warning_coast: Storm Surge Warning: Indian Pass, FL to Clearwater Beach, FL (Gulf side)
weather_observation.impacted_coast: Northern Gulf Coast from Louisiana to the Florida Panhandle, then inland across GA/SC and offshore of the Carolinas
weather_observation.wind: Breezy with occasional gusts possibly approaching tropical-storm force; overall probability of sustained 34-kt winds is low (3%).
weather_observation.storm_surge: None expected on the Atlantic side near Port Canaveral.
weather_observation.rainfall: Rain bands could drop 2-4 inches with isolated higher amounts over east-central Florida, including the port area.
weather_observation.other_hazards: Rough seas, elevated surf, and hazardous rip currents along the east-central Florida coast.
